<item>
            <title>[LU-2792] (fid_seq_in_fldb(fid_seq(fid)) ) failed: [0x200000002:0x1:0x0] is insane!</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2792</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;== sanity test 154: Open-by-FID == 21:42:22 (1385530942)&lt;br/&gt;
stat fid &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0x280002341:0x6:0x0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Message from syslogd@testnode at Nov 26 21:42:22 ...&lt;br/&gt;
 kernel:LustreError: 2347:0:(lmv_fld.c:72:lmv_fld_lookup()) ASSERTION( (fid_seq_in_fldb(fid_seq(fid)) || fid_seq_is_local_file(fid_seq(fid))) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; fid_is_sane(fid) ) failed: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0x200000002:0x1:0x0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; is insane!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Message from syslogd@testnode at Nov 26 21:42:22 ...&lt;br/&gt;
 kernel:LustreError: 2347:0:(lmv_fld.c:72:lmv_fld_lookup()) LBUG&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;It is clearly SEQ_DOT_LUSTRE(0x200000002) is not included in_fldb check, but actually we insert it into the memory fldb cache in fld_server_init.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
